news.title: Real estate, NBFCs lead salary growth in 2026: Aon study
news.para: Salaries in India are projected to rise by nine percent in 2026, led by robust growth in real estate and NBFCs. These sectors are experiencing high talent demand due to government spending and market upcycles. Overall attrition has declined, indicating improved employee stability and retention efforts across organized sectors.

news.title: Private equity investors drive $3.9 billion into Indian real estate in Jan-Sept 2025
news.para: Indian real estate attracted $1.5 billion in private equity during Q3 2025, a 32% dip year-on-year, yet year-to-date inflows remain robust. The office sector led with 39% of investments, closely followed by data centers. Foreign investors are driving over 65% of year-to-date funding, signaling strong confidence in India's long-term real estate prospects.

news.title: About ₹90,000 crore investment to double India's third party data centre capacity by FY28: ICRA
news.para: India's data centre capacity is set to double to 2,400-2,500 MW by FY28, fueled by a massive ₹90,000 crore investment pipeline. Mumbai leads the charge, contributing over half of the current operational capacity.  A proposed 20-year tax exemption policy could significantly boost this growth, making India a stronger player in the global data centre market.
